The joint statement between Prime Minister Dr. Singh and President Obama reaffirms the global strategic partnership between India and the United States. They recognize the shared values of democracy, pluralism, tolerance, openness, and respect for fundamental freedoms and human rights. The leaders commit to expanding the U.S.-India global partnership in areas such as counterterrorism, defense cooperation, nuclear disarmament, sustainable global development, clean energy, global economic revival, education, public health, and global cooperation. They also emphasize the importance of creating global institutions that are inclusive and effective in addressing the challenges of the 21st century.